rch%20suggests%20that%20hybrid%20work%20is%20still%20the%20norm%20in%20the%20tech%20industry.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%3Fh%3D2e80aac6068aad189c95f445d7befa91c2f65d6249a0dd6169828d66140a7ec1%26postID%3D66fc04b3d86164749858e533%26postSlug%3Dhybrid-work-tech-companies-rto-amazon-dell2024-10%26site%3Dbi%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.canva.com%252Fdesign%252FDAGLBzph2Ro%252FN8J1ayHcoxw4RjdoAHjz2A%252Fview%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EA%20study%20from%20Flex%20Index%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20platform%20that%20tracks%20flexible%20work%20policies%2C%20found%20most%20tech%20companies%20still%20had%20hybrid%20or%20remote%20policies%20as%20of%20this%20summer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20research%2C%20which%20analyzed%20the%20policies%20of%202%2C670%20companies%2C%20found%20that%2079%25%20of%20tech%20companies%20in%20June%20were%20%26quot%3Bfully%20flexible%2C%26quot%3B%20meaning%20they%20didn't%20mandate%20office%20time%20from%20employees%20%E2%80%94%20a%20slight%20increase%20from%20the%20same%20survey%20conducted%20in%20June%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20mere%203%25%20of%20tech%20firms%20required%20employees%20to%20be%20back%20in%20the%20office%20full%20time%2C%20compared%20with%20the%2018%25%20of%20companies%20that%20were%20%26quot%3Bstructured%20hybrid%2C%26quot%3B%20meaning%20some%20office%20days%20are%20mandated.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20picture%20was%20slightly%20different%20at%20the%20largest%20tech%20companies.%20The%20more%20employees%20a%20company%20had%2C%20the%20more%20likely%20they%20were%20to%20adopt%20a%20structured%20hybrid%20system.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJust%20shy%20of%20three-quarters%20of%20companies%20with%20more%20than%2025%2C000%20employees%20had%20adopted%20a%20structured%20hybrid%20policy%2C%20while%2037%25%20of%20tech%20firms%20with%20500%20to%205%2C000%20employees%20had%20a%20hybrid%20work%20policy.%20The%20data%20suggests%20that%20Amazon%20and%20Dell%20are%20outliers%20in%20the%20tech%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20comparison%20to%20the%20same%20research%20published%20in%20June%202023%2C%20tech%20companies%20of%20all%20sizes%20have%20been%20shifting%20a%20least%20incrementally%20toward%20hybrid%20work%2C%20with%20larger%20firms%20leading%20the%20charge.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOn%20the%20employer's%20side%2C%20I%20think%20most%20of%20them%20would%20prefer%20going%20back%20to%20regular%20office%20hours%2C%26quot%3B%20Peter%20Cappelli%2C%20a%20professor%20of%20management%20at%20Wharton%20Business%20School%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBut%20it%20is%20a%20huge%20irritation%20to%20employees%20to%20pull%20back%20a%20benefit%20employees%20really%20appreciate%2C%20especially%20because%20employers%20are%20not%20giving%20them%20anything%20in%20return%20nor%20have%20made%20much%20of%20any%20effort%20to%20persuade%20them%20why%20it's%20necessary%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20Big%20Tech%20companies%20mull%20how%20far%20to%20take%20their%20RTO%20policies%2C%20one%20thing%20is%20clear%20%E2%80%94%20hybrid%20work%20is%20the%20perk%20to%20have%20in%20the%20race%20for%20top%20talent.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22aca82825-f21f-4daa-bf17-d1e0600f72bd%5C%22%3ETalent%20wars%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EEmployees%20love%20flexibility%20at%20work.%20In%20a%20survey%20of%2017%2C087%20employees%20conducted%20by%20Stanford%20economist%20Nicholas%20Bloom%2C%20workers%20said%20they%20regarded%20the%20right%20to%20work%20two%20or%20three%20days%20a%20week%20from%20home%20as%20valuable%20as%20an%208%25%20pay%20rise.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEmployees%20under%20strict%20RTO%20mandates%20at%20Amazon%20and%20Dell%20have%20been%20vocal%20about%20their%20lack%20of%20enthusiasm%20for%20the%20new%20rules%2C%20with%20some%20at%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-dell-workers-reject-return-to-office-hybrid-work-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDell%20forsaking%20promotions%20in%20favor%20of%20remaining%20remote.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20current%20landscape%2C%20this%20likely%20means%20that%20Big%20Tech%20companies%20with%20a%20hybrid%20work%20policy%20will%20have%20an%20advantage%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20recruiting%20and%20retaining%20top%20talent.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBloom%2C%20a%20world%20authority%20on%20remote%20work%2C%20told%20BI%20he%20didn't%20expect%20other%20Big%20Tech%20firms%20to%20follow%20Amazon's%20lead%20on%20RTO%20for%20this%20reason.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHybrid%20is%20too%20profitable%20to%20abandon%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BThe%20evidence%20is%20that%20hybrid%20is%20about%20as%20efficient%20as%20fully%20in-person%20%E2%80%94%20but%20hybrid%20is%20better%20for%20recruitment%20and%20retention.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20forcing%20employees%20back%20into%20the%20office%20full%20time%20could%20drive%20higher%20turnover%2C%20which%20can%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.shrm.org%2Ftopics-tools%2Fnews%2Fall-things-work%2Freducing-employee-turnover%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebe%20costly%20for%20companies.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20tech%20world%20is%20also%20engaged%20in%20a%20brutal%20battle%20for%20talent%2C%20especially%20for%20top%20AI%20researchers.%20Last%20month%2C%20Google%20reportedly%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-noam-shazeer-deal-ai-talent-hiring-star-quarterbacks-i2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eforked%20out%20%242.7%20billion%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20a%20deal%20largely%20intended%20to%20get%20AI%20scientist%20and%20startup%20founder%20Noam%20Shazeer%20back%20at%20the%20company.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECevat%20Aksoy%2C%20associate%20director%20of%20research%20at%20the%20EBRD%20and%20associate%20professor%20of%20economics%20at%20King's%20College%20London%2C%20told%20BI%20his%20research%20shows%20a%20substantial%20portion%20of%20the%20workforce%20highly%20values%20the%20option%20to%20work%20from%20home.%20Many%20are%20willing%20to%20quit%20or%20seek%20new%20employment%20if%20ordered%20to%20return%20to%20the%20office%20full-time%2C%20he%20said.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BCompanies%20adopting%20full%20RTO%20policies%20could%20face%20challenges%20in%20retaining%20talent%2C%26quot%3B%20Aksoy%20said.%20%26quot%3BGiven%20the%20increasing%20demand%20for%20flexibility%20and%20the%20strong%20preferences%20many%20employees%20hold%2C%20we%20can%20expect%20hybrid%20work%20to%20remain%20a%20critical%20tool%20for%20companies%20seeking%20to%20stay%20competitive%20in%20attracting%20top%20talent.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20five-day%20RTO%20initiatives%20have%20their%20supporters%2C%20too.%20John%20Rossman%2C%20an%20Amazon%20executive%20in%20the%20early%202000s%2C%20told%20BI%20that%20the%20company%20is%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-office-five-days-rto-exec-andy-jassy-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emaking%20the%20right%20move%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%3Cstrong%3E%3Cspan%3E%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cspan%3E%26quot%3Bjump-start%20growth%20again.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2235ef6780-204a-46ef-9d32-1d4de7593189%5C%22%3EEfficiency%2C%20or%20else%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20last%20year%2C%20tech%20companies%20have%20been%20getting%20tough%20on%20remote%20workers%2C%20monitoring%20office%20card%20swipes%20and%20disciplining%20those%20who%20don't%20follow%20the%20rules.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20some%20large%20companies%2C%20such%20as%20Nvidia%2C%20have%20remained%20holdouts%2C%20most%20Big%20Tech%20companies%20have%20had%20hybrid%20policies%20of%20various%20degrees.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20they%20are%20also%20making%20no%20promises%20it%20will%20stay%20this%20way.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMicrosoft%20and%20Google%2C%20which%20both%20have%20a%20hybrid%20policy%20that%20allows%20employees%20to%20work%20from%20home%20at%20least%20some%20of%20the%20time%2C%20recently%20issued%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-hybrid-work-policy-amazon-rto-employees-workplace-remote-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethinly%20veiled%20threat%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20workers%3A%20keep%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmicrosoft-wont-follow-amazon-rto-unless-productivity-drops-exec-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eproductivity%20up%3C%2Fa%3E%20if%20you%20want%20to%20avoid%20a%20full-time%20office%20return.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAksoy%20said%20this%20worked%20as%20a%20way%20of%20ensuring%20accountability%20among%20tech%20workers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20likely%20a%20reminder%20to%20employees%20that%20hybrid%20work%20isn't%20guaranteed%E2%80%94it's%20tied%20to%20continued%20performance.%20This%20kind%20of%20message%20helps%20keep%20everyone%20focused%20on%20delivering%20results%20while%20giving%20the%20companies%20room%20to%20tighten%20policies%20if%20they%20start%20seeing%20any%20productivity%20issues%20or%20collaboration%20challenges%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20said%2C%20Aksoy%20still%20thinks%20it's%20unlikely%20that%20Big%20Tech%20will%20bring%20employees%20back%20for%20five%20days%20a%20week.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20benefits%20of%20hybrid%20work%2C%20both%20for%20companies%20and%20employees%2C%20are%20just%20too%20significant%2C%26quot%3B%20Aksoy%20said.%20%26quot%3BPlus%2C%20the%20hybrid%20model%20allows%20these%20companies%20to%20tap%20into%20a%20wider%20talent%20pool%20without%20being%20limited%20by%20geography.%20So%20as%20long%20as%20productivity%20stays%20up%2C%20I%20think%20hybrid%20work%20is%20here%20to%20stay%20in%20the%20tech%20world.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhybrid-work-tech-companies-rto-amazon-dell2024-10%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1727946005000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66fd4dd19e0c5c2eeee9f703%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhybrid-work-tech-companies-rto-amazon-dell2024-10%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Flexible%20work%20is%20still%20thriving%20in%20the%20tech%20industry%2C%20research%20from%20Flex%20Index%20has%20found.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22bnolan%40insider.com%20(Beatrice%20Nolan)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A5%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhybrid-work-tech-companies-rto-amazon-dell2024-10%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22AI%20coding%20tools%20mean%20there%20are%20no%20more%20junior%20software%20developers%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Image%20shows%20someone%20using%20OpenAI's%20ChatGPT%20on%20a%20laptop%20screen%20by%20starting%20to%20type%20commands%20in%20a%20search%20bar.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F650d682412dc4f001a17b266%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221803%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EGenerative%20AI%20tools%20such%20as%20ChatGPT%20have%20become%20more%20widespread%20among%20developers.%3Cp%3EFrank%20Rumpenhorst%2Fpicture%20alliance%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EAI%20coding%20tools%20like%20GitHub%20Copilot%20have%20transformed%20software%20development%20and%20productivity.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EAI%20assistants%20close%20experience%20gaps%2C%20although%20they%20may%20lead%20to%20less%20secure%2C%20bug-prone%20code.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ESoftware%20engineering%20skills%2C%20like%20creating%20smart%20architecture%20for%20code%2C%20will%20still%20be%20relevant.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EBefore%20he%20graduated%20from%20university%2C%20Jacob%20Jackson%20founded%20the%20AI%20coding%20assistant%20TabNine%20in%202018.%20Jackson%2C%20a%20computer%20science%20student%2C%20wanted%20to%20reduce%20the%20repetitive%2C%20sometimes%20boring%20tasks%20that%20a%20programmer%20could%20encounter.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20were%20just%20trying%20to%20save%20people%20keystrokes.%20There%20was%20no%20talk%20of%20AI%20designing%20or%20writing%20full%20algorithms%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHis%20startup%20eventually%20raised%20about%20%2460%20million%20and%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftechcrunch.com%2F2024%2F09%2F16%2Fai-coding-assistant-supermaven-raises-cash-from-openai-and-perplexity-founders%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eacquired%20%3C%2Fa%3Eby%20the%20Israeli%20company%20Codota%20in%202019.%20Jackson%20continued%20to%20work%20with%20AI%2C%20going%20on%20to%20intern%20and%20work%20at%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fopenai-investors-latest-funding-round-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EOpenAI%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20company%20that%20built%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Feverything-you-need-to-know-about-chat-gpt-2023-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EChatGPT%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20past%20two%20years%2C%20there%20has%20been%20a%20boom%20in%20AI%20coding%20assistants.%20OpenAI%20competitors%20have%20launched%20widely%20used%20generative%20AI%20developer%20tools%2C%20such%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcodex-github-copilot-chatgpt-openai-productivity-2023-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGitHub%20Copilot%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fanthropic-claude-chatbot-google-chatgpt-2023-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAnthropic's%20Claude%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20spike%20in%20ChatGPT%20usage%20and%20AI%20coding%20assistants%20has%20shifted%20how%20software%20developers%20do%20their%20jobs.%20Using%20AI%20to%20write%20code%20could%20also%20close%20the%20experience%20gap%20between%20more%20entry-level%20junior%20developers%20and%20senior%20developers%2C%20as%20it%20typically%20takes%20several%20years%20of%20work%20and%20even%20personal%20projects%20to%20level%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20no%20such%20thing%20as%20junior%20developers%20anymore%20because%20AI%20basically%20elevates%20everybody%20to%20be%20beyond%20that%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Nikolas%20Gauvreau%2C%20who%20has%20worked%20as%20a%20developer%20in%20Canada%20for%20more%20than%2020%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMore%20than%2097%25%20of%202%2C000%20respondents%20across%20the%20US%2C%20Brazil%2C%20Germany%2C%20and%20India%20said%20that%20they%20have%20used%20AI%20coding%20tools%20at%20work%2C%20according%20to%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fgithub.blog%2Fnews-insights%2Fresearch%2Fsurvey-ai-wave-grows%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGitHub%20survey%20published%20in%20August.%20%3C%2Fa%3EGenerative%20AI%20code%20suggestion%20tools%20can%20also%20increase%20software%20developer%20productivity%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpapers.ssrn.com%2Fsol3%2Fpapers.cfm%3Fabstract_id%3D4945566%26utm_source%3Dsubstack%26utm_medium%3Demail%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eby%2026%25%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20according%20to%20a%20study%20that%20analyzed%20data%20from%20Microsoft%2C%20Accenture%2C%20and%20an%20anonymous%20Fortune%20100%20electronics%20manufacturing%20company.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDevelopers%20say%20that%20adopting%20AI%20coding%20assistants%20will%20accelerate%20the%20field%20of%20software%20engineering%20rather%20than%20eliminate%20jobs%2C%20like%20how%20calculators%20accelerated%20math%20computing%20despite%20initial%20protests%20by%20teachers%20against%20its%20adoption.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20these%20tools%20can%20increase%20productivity%2C%20they%20may%20also%20introduce%20security%20issues%20that%20%3Cspan%3Ecreate%20more%20work%20for%20developers.%20According%20to%20a%202022%20study%20led%20by%20Stanford%20University%20cryptography%20professor%20Dan%20Boneh%2C%20people%20who%20use%20an%20AI%20assistant%20write%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fee.stanford.edu%2Fdan-boneh-and-team-find-relying-ai-more-likely-make-your-code-buggier%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Esignificantly%20less%20secure%20code%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0than%20those%20without%20access%20to%20those%20tools%3C%2Fspan%3E.%20While%20AI%20assistants%20can%20accelerate%20the%20coding%20process%2C%20they%20may%20create%20more%20bugs%20that%20require%20the%20human%20overseer%20to%20intervene.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22d6eac2da-0de8-41c4-88c4-158a2ee3f4a4%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EAI%20assistants%20can%20empower%20coders%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMost%20generative%20AI%20coding%20assistants%20focus%20on%20auto-completion%2C%20meaning%20that%20the%20tool%20suggests%20code%20as%20the%20programmer%20types.%20Other%20language%20learning%20models%20(LLMs)%20require%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-prompt-engineer-jobs-pay-salary-requirements-no-tech-background-2023-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eprompt%20engineering%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20where%20the%20user%20can%20then%20apply%20the%20AI's%20suggested%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ecode%20as%20a%20starting%20point%20for%20their%20idea%2C%20depending%20on%20the%20complexity%20of%20the%20problem%20they%20want%20to%20solve.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBefore%20the%20advent%20of%20coding%20assistants%2C%20DeepAI%20founder%20Kevin%20Baragona%20always%20had%20a%20Google%20search%20engine%20window%20pulled%20up%20in%20case%20he%20needed%20help%20solving%20a%20problem.%20Programmers%20often%20did%20research%20from%20resources%20like%20Stack%20Overflow%2C%20an%20online%20community%20forum%20where%20coders%20would%20share%20their%20solutions.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstack-overflow-crisis-future-of-online-data-ai-world-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EStack%20Overflow's%20traffic%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20fallen%20since%20the%20rise%20of%20coding%20assistants.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEvery%20few%20minutes%20when%20you're%20programming%2C%20that%20was%20sort%20of%20like%20the%20cheat%20code%20back%20then%2C%20and%20that%20just%20became%20normalized%20as%20what%20you%20do%20when%20you're%20coding%3A%20you%20Google%20a%20lot%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Baragona.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKnowing%20more%20than%20one%20coding%20language%2C%20such%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Ftech%2Fwhat-is-javascript%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EJavaScript%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Ftech%2Fwhat-is-python%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPython%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20or%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbest-programming-language-github-developers-rate-javascript-python-2021-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ERuby%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20gives%20a%20programmer%20more%20flexibility%20in%20the%20job%20market%20when%20companies%20shift%20their%20priorities.%20Learning%20a%20completely%20new%20language%2C%20though%2C%20would%20require%20lots%20of%20time%20and%20learning.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fai.meta.com%2Fblog%2Fdeep-learning-to-translate-between-programming-languages%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edeep%20learning%20models%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20allowed%20for%20more%20programming%20functions%20to%20be%20translated%20from%20one%20language%20to%20another%2C%20making%20it%20easier%20for%20developers%20to%20switch%20between%20programming%20languages%20without%20having%20to%20quickly%20learn%20them.%20Baragona%20said%20these%20tools%20make%20him%20feel%20like%20he%20knows%20%26quot%3Bevery%20programming%20language%2C%20even%20though%20I%20don't%2C%20because%20AI%20will%20help%20me%20get%20over%20the%20hump%20really%20quickly.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGauvreau%20said%20AI%20coding%20assistants%20have%20empowered%20him%20because%20he%20feels%20less%20afraid%20to%20take%20on%20more%20clients%20even%20when%20he%20may%20not%20know%20the%20solution%20yet.%20He%20said%20he's%20doubled%20the%20number%20of%20languages%20he%20learned%20in%20the%20last%20year%2C%20m