nd%20by%20an%20arbitration%20agreement%20signed%20while%20ordering%20from%20Uber%20Eats.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJohn%20McGinty%C2%A0and%20Georgia%20McGinty%20were%20involved%20in%20the%20crash%20in%20March%202022%2C%20when%20their%20Uber%20driver%20ran%20a%20red%20light%20and%20was%20struck%20by%20another%20vehicle.%20The%20collision%20left%20both%20with%20significant%20injuries%2C%20including%20multiple%20fractures%20for%20Georgia%20and%20lasting%20impairment%20for%20John.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5CnAccording%20to%20court%20filings%2C%20they%20suffered%20%E2%80%9Cserious%20physical%2C%20psychological%2C%20and%20financial%20damages.%E2%80%9D%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5CnDespite%20their%20injuries%2C%20the%20couple's%20attempt%20to%20take%20Uber%20to%20court%20for%20a%20jury%20trial%20was%20not%20allowed.%20The%20ruling%20cited%20the%20terms%20and%20conditions%2C%20including%20a%20mandatory%20arbitration%20clause%2C%20of%20Uber's%20services.%20This%20clause%20was%20accepted%20when%20the%20couple's%20daughter%20placed%20a%20separate%20order%20on%20Uber%20Eats%20using%20Georgia's%20phone.%20The%20court%20upheld%20the%20company's%20argument%20that%20by%20agreeing%20to%20Uber's%20terms%20during%20that%20transaction%2C%20the%20family%20waived%20their%20right%20to%20pursue%20claims%20in%20court.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5CnThe%20couple%20argued%20that%20it%20was%20their%20minor%20daughter%2C%20using%20Georgia's%20phone%2C%20who%20accepted%20the%20terms%20of%20service%20for%20Uber%20Eats%20by%20clicking%20a%20button%20that%20falsely%20confirmed%20she%20was%20over%2018.%20However%2C%20the%20court%20concluded%20the%20arbitration%20agreement%2C%20which%20covers%20auto%20accidents%20and%20personal%20injuries%2C%20was%20%E2%80%9Cvalid%20and%20enforceable.%E2%80%9D%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5CnIn%20response%2C%20Uber%20told%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22nofollow%2Cnoindex%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fedition.cnn.com%2F2024%2F10%2F02%2Fbusiness%2Fuber-eats-accident-lawsuit%2Findex.html%5C%22%3ECNN%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20Georgia%20%E2%80%9Cagreed%20to%20Uber's%20terms%20of%20use%2C%20including%20the%20arbitration%20agreement%2C%20on%20multiple%20occasions%2C%E2%80%9D%20and%20even%20took%20rides%20after%20agreeing.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%E2%80%9CWhile%20the%20plaintiffs%20continue%20to%20tell%20the%20press%20that%20it%20was%20their%20daughter%20who%20ordered%20Uber%20Eats%20and%20accepted%20the%20terms%20of%20use%2C%20it's%20worth%20noting%20that%20in%20court%20they%20could%20only%20%E2%80%98surmise'%20that%20that%20was%20the%20case%20but%20could%20not%20recall%20whether%20%E2%80%98their%20daughter%20ordered%20food%20independently%20or%20if%20Georgia%20assisted%2C%26quot%3B%20CNN%20quoted%20a%20spokesperson%20as%20saying.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5CnThe%20couple%20expressed%20disappointment%20in%20a%20statement%2C%20saying%20they%20were%20%E2%80%9Csurprised%20and%20heartbroken%E2%80%9D%20by%20the%20ruling.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20are%20horrified%20at%20what%20the%20court's%20decision%20suggests%3A%20A%20large%20corporation%20like%20Uber%20can%20avoid%20being%20sued%20in%20a%20court%20of%20law%20by%20injured%20consumers%20because%20of%20contractual%20language%20buried%20in%20a%20dozen-page-long%20user%20agreement%20concerning%20services%20unrelated%20to%20the%20one%20that%20caused%20the%20consumers'%20injuries%2C%E2%80%9D%20CNN%20quoted%20the%20McGintys%20as%20saying.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5CnPreviously%2C%20a%20lower%20court%20said%20that%20Uber's%20arbitration%20clause%20was%20not%20enforceable%2C%20arguing%20the%20terms%20of%20service%20pop-up%20did%20not%20inform%20Georgia%20that%20she%20was%20waiving%20her%20right%20to%20a%20judicial%20trial.%20However%2C%20following%20an%20appeal%20from%20Uber%2C%20the%20appellate%20court%20reversed%20that%20decision%2C%20siding%20with%20the%20company.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5CnThe%20McGintys'%20legal%20team%20is%20considering%20further%20action%2C%20with%20their%20lawyers%20telling%20CNN%20that%20they%20will%20%E2%80%9Clikely%E2%80%9D%20petition%20the%20New%20Jersey%20Supreme%20Court.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1727931660000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-10%2Fn6q13e8g_uber-eats_625x300_03_October_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fcouple-injured-in-uber-accident-cant-sue-company-due-to-uber-eats-order-6704782%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22John%20McGinty%20and%20his%20wife%2C%20Georgia%2C%20were%20involved%20in%20an%20accident%20in%20March%202022%20when%20their%20Uber%20driver%20ran%20a%20red%20light%20and%20was%20struck%20by%20another%20vehicle.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fcouple-injured-in-uber-accident-cant-sue-company-due-to-uber-eats-order-6704782%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Dominican%20Republic%20'to%20deport%20up%20to%2010%2C000%20migrants%20a%20week'%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1727931320000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fichef.bbci.co.uk%2Fnews%2F1024%2Fbranded_news%2F5e8f%2Flive%2F4ec67550-813a-11ef-822c-a50726bfda2e.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2Fc20jepjrx74o%231%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Many%20Haitian%20migrants%20are%20fleeing%20extreme%20gang%20violence%20and%20poverty%20in%20the%20capital%20Port-au-Prince.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A39%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2Fc20jepjrx74o%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-bbc-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2Fc20jepjrx74o.amp%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2Fc20jepjrx74o.amp%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Israel-Hezbollah%20conflict%3A%20How%20hard%20liners%20influence%20Netanyahu%20govt%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1727929658000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-113893988%2Cimgsize-61554.cms%22%2C%22origin